    "title": "The Wind Waste Clock",
    "lastUpdated": "2026-04-14",
    "source": "NESO Annual Balancing Costs Report, Renewable Energy Foundation, Elexon BMRS, DESNZ",
    "period": "2020–2025 annual data; 2026 running estimate",
    "methodology": "Constraint payments are compensation paid to wind farms instructed to reduce output when the transmission network cannot carry the generated power. The B6 Anglo-Scottish boundary is the primary bottleneck."
  },
  "contextSentences": {
    "headline": "The UK pays wind farms billions to switch off — because the grid can't carry the power they generate.",
    "subtext": "Scottish wind farms produce more energy than the transmission network can handle. Rather than upgrading the grid, we pay them constraint payments to stop generating. Then we pay gas plants to fill the gap."
  },
